        <div n="096-ROGP" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-1"> The Queen has lately lost a part&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-2"> Of her entirely English heart,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-3"> For want of which by way of botch,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-4"> She pieced it up again with Scotch.</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-5"> Blessed revolution, which creates</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-6"> Divided hearts, united states.</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-7"> See how the double nation lies;</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-8"> Like a rich coat with skirts of frieze:</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-9"> As if a man in making posies</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-10"> Should bundle thistles up with roses.</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-11"> Whoever yet a union saw</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-12"> Of kingdoms, without faith or law.</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-13"> Henceforward let no statesman dare,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-14"> A kingdom to a ship compare;</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-15"> Lest he should call our commonweal,</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-16"> A vessel with a double keel:</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-17"> Which just like ours, new rigged and manned,</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-18"> And got about a league from land,</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-19"> By change of wind to leeward side</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-20"> The pilot knew not how to guide.</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-21"> So tossing faction will o'erwhelm</l><l n="22" xml:id="spp-096-ROGP-line-22"> Our crazy double-bottomed realm.096-ROGP   </l></lg></div>
